<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Questionable status. In the Mediterranean only reported from Greece (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bogdanos, Costantinos" journalOrPublisher="Thalassographica" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="77 - 105" title="The macrozoobenthos of an Aegean Embayment" volume="6" year="1983">Bogdanos and Satsmadjis 1983</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bogdanos, Costantinos" journalOrPublisher="Thalassographica" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="37 - 71" title="The Patraikos Gulf bottom fauna" volume="10" year="1987">Bogdanos and Satsmadjis 1987</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Simboura, Nomiki" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. National and Kapodistrian University of Athens, Athens" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Θαλάσσοι μακροβενθικοί Πολύxαιτοι (AnnelidaPolychaeta) της Ελλάδας: Συστηματική, Οικολογία, Ζωογεωγραφία" year="1996">Simboura 1996</bibRefCitation>
; full reference list in Suppl. material 2). Distributed in the Indian Ocean and tropical Atlantic. As the species shows a wide polymorphism of the prostomial antenna (
<bibRefCitation author="Strelzov, Vladimir" journalOrPublisher="Akademia Nauk, Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Mnogoshchetinkovye chervi semeistva Paraonidae Cerruti, 1909" year="1973">Strelzov 1973</bibRefCitation>
), Mediterranean specimens could have been misidentified and belong in fact to 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Paraonidae" genus="Aricidea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aricidea (Strelzovia) claudiae" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="claudiae" subGenus="Strelzovia">Aricidea (Strelzovia) claudiae</taxonomicName>
Laubier, 1967 (J. Langeneck, pers. comm).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
